local_llm_description: The image presents a graph that displays the external reference for a 5V power supply current, with the x-axis representing time and the y-axis representing the current in milliampere-hours (mAh). The graph shows a steady increase in the supply current over time, indicating that the device is receiving an adequate amount of power.

external_llm_result.title: Power Supply Current vs Power Supply Voltage
external_llm_result.summary: Power supply current increases with AVDD from about 0.73 mA at 2.7V to about 1.09 mA at 5.5V.
